IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: LED BY MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY STUDENTS, WE ARE THE INCLUSIVE VOICE FOR ALL FUTURE, CURRENT, AND FORMER STUDENTS. WE ACTIVELY WORK TO REPRESENT AND SUPPORT MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY STUDENTS AND ADVOCATE AT A SYSTEM, LOCAL, STATE, AND FEDERAL LEVEL FOR HIGHER EDUCATION POLICIES THAT MAKE A POSITIVE IMPACT FOR OUR STUDENTS AND COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: LED BY MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY STUDENTS, WE ARE THE INCLUSIVE VOICE FOR ALL FUTURE, CURRENT, AND FORMER STUDENTS. WE ACTIVELY WORK TO REPRESENT AND SUPPORT MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY STUDENTS AND ADVOCATE AT A CAMPUS, STATE, AND FEDERAL LEVEL FOR HIGHER EDUCATION POLICIES THAT MAKE A POSITIVE IMPACT FOR OUR STUDENTS AND COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.Desc: STUDENT PROGRAMMING: STUDENTS UNITED INFORMS, ORGANIZES AND REPRESENTS STUDENTS ON THE SEVEN MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY CAMPUSES ABOUT ISSUES THEY CHOOSE SUCH AS CIVIC ENGAGMENT AND HIGHER EDUCATION AFFORDABILITY INCLUDING, TUITION, FEES AND TEXBOOKS, DIVERSITY AND INCLUSIVE EXCELLENCE AND STUDENT SUCCESS AND WELLNESS. STUDENTS WORK WITH THE MINNESOTA STATE COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES TO CREATE AND IMPLEMENT STUDENT-FOCUSED POLICIES AND PRACTICES. WE ALSO FOCUS ON STUDENT LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT WITH STUDENTS INVOLVED IN STUDENTS UNITED.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: STUDENT ADVOCACY: STUDENTS UNITED PROVIDES INFORMATION TO STUDENTS ABOUT THE ISSUES THAT AFFECTS THEIR LIVES AS STUDENTS, PROVIDES STUDENTS OPPORTUNITIES TO PARTICIPATE IN ADVOCACY AT MANY LEVELS AND REPRESENTS STUDENT POSITIONS TO POLICY MAKERS. WE ADVOCATE AT A SYSTEM, STATE, AND FEDERAL LEVEL ON A WIDE VARIETY OF HIGHER EDUCATION ISSUES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: SCHOLARSHIP DISBURSEMENT: STUDENTS UNITED OFFERS 7 SCHOLARSHIPS TO ASSIST STUDENTS WITH THEIR HIGHER EDUCATION EXPENSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HOSTS AN ANNUAL ADVOCACY CONFERENCE, WHICH PROVIDES LEARNING SESSION AND STUDENT ACTIONS RELATED TO HIGHER EDUCATION POLICY. STUDENTS UNITED ALSO HOSTS AN ADVOCACY DAY AT THE MINNESOTA STATE CAPITOL WHERE STUDENT MEET WITH THEIR ELECTED REPRESENTATIVES TO DISCUSS THE ORGANIZATION'S STATE LEGISLATIVE AGENDA. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO BRINGS STUDENTS ON AN ANNUAL TRIP TO WASHINGTON, D.C. TO MEET WITH POLICY MAKERS, COALITIONS AND ELECTED REPRESENTATIVES ON THE FEDERAL LEVEL. STUDENTS UNITED ALSO MEETS REGULARLY WITH MINNESOTA STATE SYSTEM POLICY MAKERS ON A MONTHLY BASIS. THIS YEAR, ALL THESE SYSTEM, STATE, AND FEDERAL ACTIVITIES WERE VIRTUAL.

STUDENTS UNITED IS THE FISCAL AGENT FOR THE MINNESOTA STATE UNIVERSITY SYSTEM JOB FAIR. UNDER THIS RELATIONSHIP, STUDENTS UNITED EXECUTES TRANSACTIONS SOLELY UNDER THEIR DIRECTION. SINCE THE MONIES ARE NOT UNDER STUDENTS UNITED'S CONTROL, THEY ARE REPORTED AS A LIABILITY ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS UNTIL SPENT AS DIRECTED.
STUDENTS UNITED'S ENDOWMENTS CONSIST OF FUNDS ESTABLISHED FOR A VARIETY OF PURPOSES. ITS ENDOWMENTS INCLUDE DONOR-RESTRICTED ENDOWMENT FUNDS.

STUDENTS UNITED IS A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION THAT IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND IS CLASSIFIED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AS OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. STUDENTS UNITED IS ALSO EXEMPT FROM MINNESOTA FRANCHISE OR INCOME TAX. STUDENTS UNITED FILES FORM 990, RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX. STUDENTS UNITED IS REQUIRED TO ASSESS WHETHER AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS EXISTS AND IF THERE SHOULD BE RECOGNITION OF A RELATED BENEFIT OR LIABILITY IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. STUDENTS UNITED HAS DETERMINED THERE ARE NO AMOUNTS TO RECORD AS ASSETS OR LIABILITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.
AGENCY EXPENSES FOR MN UNIVERSITY JOB FAIR -16,428.
STUDENTS SELECTED FOR THE SCHOLARSHIPS ARE REQUIRED TO SUBMIT A MID-INTERNSHIP SUMMARY REPORT AND ONE JOURNAL ENTRY BEFORE THEY RECEIVE THE FINAL 25% OF THEIR AWARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DELEGATED THE VICE CHAIR AND TREASURER ELECTIONS TO A HIRING COMMITTEE OF 14 STUDENTS. THIS COMMITTEE'S TASK WAS TO ELECT THE VICE CHAIR AND TREASURER FOR FY22.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TREASURER POSITION HAS BEEN UPDATED TO THE TREASURER/SECRETARY WITH ADDED DUTIES. THE DELEGATES ASSEMBLY COMMITTEE HAS BEEN UPDATED TO CLARIFY WHO CAN PARTICIPATE IN A DELEGATES ASSEMBLY AND HOW OFTEN A DELEGATES ASSEMBLY MEETING OCCURS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DIRECTORS ARE ELECTED BY STUDENTS AT THE SEVEN STATE UNIVERSITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS ARE SELECTED BY THEIR STUDENT GOVERNMENTS ON EACH CAMPUS, BOARD OFFICERS ARE ELECTED BY STUDENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS SENT TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO THE BOARD MEETING FOR THEIR REVIEW AND APPROVAL BEFORE THE TAX RETURN IS SIGNED AND FILED WITH THE IRS. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE GIVEN THE CHANCE TO ASK ANY QUESTIONS ABOUT THE TAX RETURN WHEN THE ACCOUNTING FIRM PRESENTS THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT IS DIRECTED NOT ONLY TO DIRECTORS AND OFFICERS, BUT TO ALL EMPLOYEES WHO CAN INFLUENCE THE ACTIONS OF STUDENTS UNITED. A MATERIAL CONFLICTING INTEREST MAY BE DEFINED AS AN INTEREST, DIRECT OR INDIRECT, WITH ANY PERSONS AND FIRMS ENGAGING IN BUSINESS WITH STUDENTS UNITED, COMPETING OR AFFINITY ORGANIZATIONS, OR FAMILY MEMBERS, FRIENDS AND OTHER EMPLOYEES. THE EXISTENCE OF ANY INTERESTS SHALL BE DISCLOSED BEFORE ANY TRANSACTION IS CONSUMMATED. IT SHALL BE THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BOARD, OFFICERS AND MANAGEMENT TO SCRUTINIZE THEIR TRANSACTIONS AND OUTSIDE INTERESTS FOR POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND TO IMMEDIATELY MAKE SUCH DISCLOSURES. THE BOARD SHALL DETERMINE WHETHER A CONFLICT EXISTS AND IS MATERIAL, AND IN THE PRESENCE OF AN EXISTING MATERIAL CONFLICT, WHETHER THE CONTEMPLATED TRANSACTION MAY BE AUTHORIZED AS JUST, FAIR, AND REASONABLE TO THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS USED THE MINNESOTA COUNCIL OF NONPROFIT SALARY SURVEY FOR COMPARABILITY DATA, DISCUSSED THE SALARY IN EXECUTIVE SESSION AND PASSED A BOARD MOTION SETTING THE SALARY. THE COMPARABILITY DATA PROVIDED IS THE MINNESOTA COUNCIL OF NONPROFIT SALARY SURVEY AND SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR SALARIES.THE ORGANIZATION HAS THE OFFICERS DOCUMENT THE DELIBERATION AND DECISION WHILE IN EXECUTIVE SESSION. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR UTILIZES THE MINNESOTA COUNCIL OF NONPROFIT SALARY SURVEY FOR COMPARABILITY DATA AS WELL AS BENCHMARKS WITH SIMILAR ORGANIZATION TO DETERMINE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES. THE PROCESS DESCRIBED HERE WAS LAST COMPLETED IN 2022

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE PROVIDED ELECTRONICALLY TO BOARD MEMBERS, WHO MAY DISTRIBUTE THEM. GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE ON THE WEBSITE.
THE AUDIT OVERSIGHT PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
